---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/index.css";

const canonical = "https://www.ashwingupta.dev/work/pageindexollama";
const githubUrl = "https://github.com/ughshwin/PageIndexOllama";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="PageIndexOllama — Local-First Fork of PageIndex | Ashwin Gupta"
  description="Provider-agnostic tree-RAG. Offline execution via Ollama, llama.cpp, and vLLM. Finish-reason normalization eliminates silent traversal corruption on provider switch."
  canonical={canonical}
>
  <div class="spatial-scene">
    <div class="thinking-scroll">
      <div class="thinking-body">

        <a href="/#projects" class="back-link">← Back to projects</a>

        <header class="th-header">
          <div class="th-badge">Shipped · Open Source</div>
          <h1 class="th-title">PageIndexOllama — Local-First Fork of PageIndex</h1>
          <p class="th-subtitle">Tree-RAG freed from provider lock-in. Offline execution across Ollama, llama.cpp, and vLLM — finish-reason normalization makes traversal correctness independent of which runtime answers.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="th-divider"></div>

        <section class="th-section">
          <h2 class="th-section-title">The Problem</h2>
          <p class="th-body">
            PageIndex's tree-RAG was hardwired to OpenAI's API contract — inline prompt strings, non-normalized completion handling. Any provider switch corrupted recursive traversal silently, with errors surfacing only at collapse. All inference required a live API key, blocking offline or air-gapped execution entirely. Token encoding differences across providers produced inconsistent chunk boundaries with no visible signal.
          </p>
          <p class="th-body">
            The failure mode was particularly dangerous: traversal would proceed, produce output, and only reveal the corruption at the final collapse stage. There was no early signal that the provider difference had invalidated the intermediate steps.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="th-section">
          <h2 class="th-section-title">The Approach</h2>
          <p class="th-body">
            Forked and refactored with a <strong>provider-routing abstraction</strong> resolved via environment variables. A <strong>finish-reason normalization layer</strong> stabilizes recursive traversal across model outputs — traversal depends on stable internal contracts, not whichever runtime answered. Prompts externalized into a registry loader, removing the coupling between prompt content and provider expectations.
          </p>
          <p class="th-body">
            The key insight: tree-RAG correctness depends on finish-reason semantics, not provider identity. Normalizing finish reasons before they enter traversal logic makes the rest of the pipeline provider-agnostic. Bounded async concurrency across TOC generation and summarization prevents resource saturation on constrained hardware. Hierarchical fallback handles cases where the primary chunking strategy exceeds available VRAM.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="th-section">
          <h2 class="th-section-title">Outcomes</h2>
          <p class="th-body">
            Fully offline tree-RAG with Ollama — no API keys. Seamless provider switching across Ollama, llama.cpp, and vLLM via stable internal contracts, with no traversal corruption on change. Vendor lock-in eliminated. Fallback chunk policies handle constrained VRAM and RAM without requiring manual tuning.
          </p>
        </section>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">
          <a href={githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-link">
            ↗ View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="th-footer">
          <span>© 2026 Ashwin Gupta · AI Engineer · Bangalore, India</span>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  body {
    background: #060608;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .thinking-scroll {
    overflow-y: auto;
    height: 100vh;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .thinking-body {
    width: max(320px, 60vw);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 0 8rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .thinking-body {
      padding: 7rem 0 8rem;
    }
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); }

  .th-header { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  .th-badge {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.54rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #22d3ee;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .th-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #fafaf8;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .th-subtitle {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    margin: 0;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .th-divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .th-section { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }

  .th-section-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #fafaf8;
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .th-body {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .th-body strong { color: #e8e0d0; font-weight: 600; }

  .cta-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #22d3ee;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.35);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 8px 14px;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .cta-link:hover { background: rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.08); }

  .th-footer {
    margin-top: 6rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>
